{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-blog-js","path":"/blog/neat_font/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"url":"https://poetry.me.uk"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I have found myself wishing I could tweak the style of the fonts that I have been using for poetry presentation. This eventually culminated with an attempt to create my own font that had all the characteristics I sought.</p>\n<p>I started by drawing the character map by hand and then digitizing the characters to create the font. Working on this font quickly made me appreciate the non trivial problems of style consistency and character spacing.</p>\n<h4>Tools used:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>GIMP</li>\n<li>potrace</li>\n<li>FontForge</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is a bold italic poster font, with extra emphases on capitalised letters. The font is called <code>neat</code></p>\n<p><a href=\"/download/neat_font.ttf\">Download the Font.ttf</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/29007/neat_font.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Neat Font\"\n        title=\"Neat Font\"\n        src=\"/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/5a190/neat_font.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/772e8/neat_font.png 200w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/e17e5/neat_font.png 400w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/5a190/neat_font.png 800w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/c1b63/neat_font.png 1200w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/29007/neat_font.png 1600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","excerpt":"I have found myself wishing I could tweak the style of the fonts that I have been using for poetry presentation. This eventually culminated with an attempt to create my own font that had all the characteristics I sought. I started by drawing theâ€¦","rawMarkdownBody":"\nI have found myself wishing I could tweak the style of the fonts that I have been using for poetry presentation. This eventually culminated with an attempt to create my own font that had all the characteristics I sought.  \n\nI started by drawing the character map by hand and then digitizing the characters to create the font. Working on this font quickly made me appreciate the non trivial problems of style consistency and character spacing.  \n\n#### Tools used:  \n\n- GIMP\n- potrace\n- FontForge\n\nThis is a bold italic poster font, with extra emphases on capitalised letters. The font is called `neat`  \n\n[Download the Font.ttf](/download/neat_font.ttf)\n\n![Neat Font](./neat_font.png)\n","fields":{"slug":"/blog/neat_font/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"December 29, 2020","title":"Neat Font","tags":null,"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/ee604/neat_font.png","srcSet":"/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/69585/neat_font.png 200w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/497c6/neat_font.png 400w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/ee604/neat_font.png 800w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/f3583/neat_font.png 1200w,\n/static/3fdd353d6d5a8ab19da495856c15bb79/5707d/neat_font.png 1600w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px","presentationHeight":800,